items.name: format
items.text: The color format to for the value config. The value can be set using any supported format or named color, but the stored value will always be in this format. Supported formats are: - hex6 - For example "ffaa00" (Note: does not preserve transparency). - hex8 - For eaxmple "ffaa00ff" - the last 2 digits represent transparency - #hex6 - For example "#ffaa00" (same as "hex6" but with a leading "#"). - #hex8 - For example "#ffaa00ff" (same as "hex8" but with a leading "#"). - HEX6 - Same as "hex6" but upper case. - HEX8 - Same as "hex8" but upper case. - #HEX6 - Same as "#hex6" but upper case. - #HEX8 - Same as "#hex8" but upper case.

items.name: value
items.text: The initial color to highlight; see format for supported formats.

items.name: color
items.text: This config property is used internally by the UI to maintain the full color. Changes to this config are automatically reflected in value and vise-versa. Setting value can, however, cause the alpha to be dropped if the new value does not contain an alpha component.
